    "recap_headline": "Brown University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "SOUTH ORANGE, N.J. \u2013\nA three-run sixth inning for Seton Hall helped the Pirates defeat Brown baseball by a score of 5-2 on Friday afternoon. Seton Hall outhit Brown 9-8 in the game as seven different Bears recorded hits.\nSenior\nDJ Dillehay\nhad two hits for Brown, sophomore\nChristian Butera\nhad an RBI single, senior\nLogan Meusy\nadded an RBI double, while junior\nAndrew Hanlon\nand sophomore\nAlex Benevento\neach had a hit and run scored. Sophomore\nMatt Wilmarth\ntossed 1.2 scoreless innings of relief, without issuing a walk.\nBrown struck for single runs in both the third and fourth innings to take a 2-0 lead. Hanlon singled and later scored on a double by Meusy in the third. Benevento then led off the fourth with a single, stole second and came home on a single up the middle by Butera.\nSeton Hall got on the board in the fifth with a leadoff triple and a sac fly. The Pirates then took control with three runs in the sixth. Following a leadoff walk and a groundout, SHU used four consecutive hits including a two-run double and a single to take a 4-2 lead before a double play got Brown out of the inning.\nA leadoff walk and two-out single plated another insurance run for SHU in the eighth.\nThe same two teams will continue their three-game weekend series tomorrow afternoon, March 14 with the first pitch scheduled for 1 p.m.\nBROWN UNIVERSITY SPORTS FOUNDATION\nThe Brown University Sports Foundation (BUSF) is the backbone of our athletics program, playing a crucial role in enhancing the student-athlete experience.\u00a0This\u00a0is possible through philanthropic support from our alumni, parents, fans, and friends.\u00a0Your\u00a0gift through the Sports Foundation can immediately impact today's Brown Bears, helping them excel in the classroom, in competition, and, most importantly, in the community. Please click\nhere\nto learn more about how\u00a0you\u00a0can support the Bears.\nFOLLOW US ON SOCIAL\nFor the latest on Brown Athletics, please follow\n@BrownU_Bears\non X and\n@BrownU_Bears\non Instagram. Like\nBrownUBears\non Facebook and subscribe to the\nBrownAthletics\nYouTube channel."
